"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-28-paralympics-use-agitos-logo-not-olympic-rings-21504767\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"With three curved swishes in red, blue and green, theParalympicsymbol certainly looks slick.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is more to the Agitos logo, which is on display at theParis 2024 games,\\u00a0than\\u00a0three colourful lines, with the design signifying the four core values of the Paralympics: courage, determination, inspiration and equality.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 119, \"end\": 125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agitos\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Red, blue and green\\u00a0were chosen, as they are the colours most used in flags around the world, and the curve in the line shows 'spirit in movement'.\", \"from\": 323, \"to\": 470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Agitos' itself means 'I move' in Latin.\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 473, \"end\": 479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agitos\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The name symbolises the motion of the Paralympic athletes - but also the Paralympic movement as a whole and the\\u00a0athletes who travel\\u00a0to compete.\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 586, \"end\": 605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic movement\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But why are not theOlympicrings used, as well?\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These are the ParalympicGames, after all.\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 746, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's what you need to know.\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With many matching sporting events at the Paralympics, you'd think the logos would match, too.\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 873, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, both Games see competitions in archery, athletics, canoe sprint, cycling, equestrian, football, judo, powerlifting, rowing, sailing, shooting, volleyball, swimming, table tennis, triathlon, basketball, fencing, rugby and tennis.\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 1116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_sprint\", \"score\": 0.9999307607083162, \"rank\": 6.924408617536357e-05, \"text\": \"sprint\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_sprint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_sprint\"}, {\"begin\": 962, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para-equestrian\", \"score\": 0.9992965797462929, \"rank\": 0.0007010584155024807, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para-equestrian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para-equestrian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As it happens, the logos were quite similar once upon a time, until 2003.\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1191, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The original symbol was based on a Korean tae-geuk decoration, and featured blue, black, red, yellow and green symbols - the same colours used at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1228, \"end\": 1234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9985804493266871, \"rank\": 0.001417168796145427, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was unveiled during Seoul 1988, and was said to signify the reality from which all things and values originate.\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1377, \"end\": 1387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 0.9999977084647861, \"rank\": 2.291540468589782e-06, \"text\": \"Seoul 1988\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Paralympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sadly, the design was seen as too similar to the Olympic rings - and so it was ditched, and the Agitos logo was created, first used in 2004.\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1566, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agitos\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why can not it be similar?\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, the International Olympic Committee (IOC) object to any symbol resembling the Olympic rings - or anyone trying to use the actual Olympic rings for their own purposes.\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1811, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1649, \"end\": 1686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, that explains the significant difference between the Olympic symbol and the Paralympic one.\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 1908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:When do the Tokyo 2020 Paralympics start?\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1932, \"end\": 1954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tokyo 2020 Paralympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Paralympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1932, \"end\": 1937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999932720637706, \"rank\": 6.727232493485292e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Team GB Paralympics legend David Weir: 'I feel a lot calmer and less angry at 42'  ArrowMORE:Athlete 'not disabled enough' for Paralympics is considering amputating a leg  Follow Metro across our social channels, onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram  Share your views in the comments below  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999427926870718, \"rank\": 5.66088291569414e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2564, \"end\": 2570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"score\": 0.6784377202962604, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punchy\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 2676, \"to\": 2807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2868, \"entities\": []}]}"